raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "httpie" %}
{% set version = "3.2.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c9c0032ca3a8d62492b7231b2dd83d94becf3b71baf8a4bbcd9ed1038537e3ec

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  entry_points:
    - http = httpie.__main__:main
    - https = httpie.__main__:main
    - httpie = httpie.manager.__main__:main

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.8
    - pip
  run:
    - __{{ target_os }}
    - python >=3.8
    - charset-normalizer >=2.0.0
    - colorama >=0.2.4  # [win]
    - defusedxml >=0.6.0
    - multidict >=4.7.0
    - pip
    - pygments >=2.5.2
    - requests >=2.22.0
    - requests-toolbelt >=0.9.1
    - rich >=9.10.0
    - setuptools


test:
  imports:
    - httpie
  commands:
    - pip check
    - http --help
    - https --help
    - httpie --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://httpie.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: a CLI, cURL-like tool for humans
  description: |
    HTTPie (pronounced aitch-tee-tee-pie) is a command line HTTP client. Its
    goal is to make CLI interaction with web services as human-friendly as
    possible. It provides a simple http command that allows for sending
    arbitrary HTTP requests using a simple and natural syntax, and displays
    colorized output. HTTPie can be used for testing, debugging, and generally
    interacting with HTTP servers.
  doc_url: https://httpie.org/doc
  dev_url: https://github.com/jakubroztocil/httpie

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - djsutherland
    - ocefpaf
    - honnorat
